@woodsworths_dilemma
title: There is no clear governing majority.
subtitle: King Woodsworth faces a dilemma.
view-if: king == "Woodsworth" and (grand_coalition < 50 or grand_coalition_failed == 1)

King Woodsworth faces a dilemma. He desperately desires a socialist or at least democratic government, but the electoral results are not there for such. Article 48 has been used by George V to promulgate anti-democratic and anti-worker policies; can Article 48 be used for good as well as evil?

- @emergency_woodsworth: We will form an emergency government with Woodsworth's support.
- @new_elections: We will have new elections.
- @new_grand_coalition
- @left_coalition
- @popular_front_coalition
- @far_right_coalition



@emergency_woodsworth
title: We will form an emergency government with Woodsworth's support.
subtitle: This may have the effect of inflamming public sentiment against us, and the reactionaries will be against us each step of the way.
on-arrival: sa_strength += 100; sh_strength += 100; in_emergency_government = 1

Yes, an emergency minority government, with the support of the CCF. Who should lead this emergency minority government?

- @woodsworth_emergency_chancellor: J.S. Woodsworth for Chancellor-King!
- @gardiner_emergency_chancellor: Robert Gardiner for emergency Chancellor.
- @bruning_emergency_chancellor: Brüning of the Center Party, as a goodwill gesture toward the bourgeoisie.
- @wirth_emergency_chancellor: Joseph Wirth of the Center Party, as a gesture of republican unity.

@woodsworth_emergency_chancellor
subtitle: This is unprecedented.
view-if: not historical_mode or not ccf_prussia
on-arrival: chancellor = "Woodsworth"; chancellor_party = "CCF"; ccf_in_government = 1; pro_republic -= 5; foreign_minister_party = "CCF"; interior_minister_party = "CCF"; justice_minister_party = "CCF"; labor_minister_party = "CCF"; reichswehr_minister_party = "CCF"; economic_minister_party = "CCF"; finance_minister_party = "CCF"; agriculture_minister_party = "CCF"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.1; 

Our experts have checked the constitution, and have discovered that there is no specific prohibition against the Chancellor also being the King (the King may not be a member of the Reichstag; there is no law saying that the Chancellor *must* be a member of the Reichstag).

Thus, we have Chancellor-King J.S. Woodsworth. He claims that he will resign as soon as the economic-political crisis is over. The right-wing parties, who were once clamoring to replace parliamentary rule with dictatorship or monarchy, are now clamoring for the restoration of democracy.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence: The Nazis immediately call a no-confidence vote against us...

@gardiner_emergency_chancellor
subtitle: The Communists are warming to him...
on-arrival: chancellor = "Gardiner"; chancellor_party = "CCF"; ccf_in_government = 1; pcc_relation += 5; foreign_minister_party = "CCF"; interior_minister_party = "CCF"; justice_minister_party = "CCF"; labor_minister_party = "CCF"; reichswehr_minister_party = "CCF"; economic_minister_party = "CCF"; finance_minister_party = "CCF"; agriculture_minister_party = "CCF"; reichswehr_loyalty -= 0.1;

We have appointed Robert Gardiner as emergency chancellor. The Communists consider him less objectionable than the alternatives, although it is unclear whether they will tolerate this government.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence


@bruning_emergency_chancellor
on-arrival: chancellor = "Brüning"; chancellor_party = "RPC"; ccf_in_government = 1; rpc_relation += 10; foreign_minister_party = "CCF"; interior_minister_party = "CCF"; justice_minister_party = "CCF"; labor_minister_party = "CCF"; reichswehr_minister_party = "CCF"; economic_minister_party = "CCF"; finance_minister_party = "CCF"; agriculture_minister_party = "CCF" 

The Center Party is pleased, and somewhat surprised, that we have appointed [+ chancellor +] as chancellor.

- @far_right_coup
- @emergency_no_confidence

@wirth_emergency_chancellor
